  "title": "Pointing presumes a pointer who can say what they see, but much expertise is tacit — in a field whose experts cannot articulate their own features, how does a learner extract them: contrast alone, or machines that learned the discrimination naming it back?",
  "url": "https://cambridgetcg.github.io/castle-gate/rooms/naming-the-tacit",
  "summary": "The master sexes the chick and cannot say how; someone else, watching, finds the one word he was missing — and a minute later the novice can do it too.",
